HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 724
By Hemmer
A RESOLUTION to honor Clay Jackson upon his being conferred
the Order of the Rising Sun, Gold and Silver
Rays by the Consulate-General of Japan.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should recognize
those individuals whose service and dedication have strengthened the cultural, civic, and
international ties of the State of Tennessee; and
WHEREAS, one such individual is Clay Jackson, who has devoted many years to
promoting Japanese culture in Tennessee through civic leadership and community
engagement; and
WHEREAS, on September 4, 2025, at a formal conferment ceremony held at the official
residence of the Consul-General of Japan in Nashville, the Order of the Rising Sun, Gold and
Silver Rays was conferred upon Mr. Jackson, one of Japan's highest honors bestowed upon
civilians; and
WHEREAS, the Order of the Rising Sun, established in 1875, is conferred in recognition
of distinguished achievements and exceptional contributions to international relations, promotion
of Japanese culture, and the advancement of mutual understanding and goodwill between
Japan and other nations; and
WHEREAS, Clay Jackson, together with his wife, Cathy Jackson, served with distinction
as co-chairs of the Nashville Cherry Blossom Festival Advisory Committee, providing leadership
and vision that helped elevate the festival into a meaningful and enduring celebration of
Japanese culture and friendship; and
WHEREAS, through his long-standing involvement in the Nashville Cherry Blossom
Festival, cherry tree planting initiatives throughout the Nashville area, and his support of
HJR0724
010676
- 1 -

Cheekwood Botanical Garden, Clay Jackson has played a significant role in fostering cultural
appreciation, civic pride, and environmental stewardship within this State; and
WHEREAS, beyond these efforts, Mr. Jackson has contributed substantially to the
evolution of mutual understanding and friendly relations between Japan and the State of
Tennessee, serving as a bridge between communities and strengthening bonds that extend
beyond culture to include education, tourism, and economic cooperation; and
WHEREAS, during the conferment ceremony, Consul-General Watanabe commended
Clay Jackson for his contributions to introducing Japanese culture in the United States and for
his unwavering commitment to promoting friendship and mutual understanding between Japan
and the United States; and
WHEREAS, the ceremony was further marked by remarks from United States Senator
Bill Hagerty, who expressed gratitude for Mr. Jackson's service as a bridge between Japan and
Tennessee, and from Nashville Mayor Freddie O'Connell, who highlighted the role of the Cherry
Blossom Festival in strengthening cultural and economic bonds between the two communities;
and
WHEREAS, through his leadership, generosity, and commitment to cultural diplomacy,
Clay Jackson has brought honor to the State of Tennessee while exemplifying the values of
service, cooperation, and international friendship; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor and commend Clay Jackson upon his being conferred the Order
of the Rising Sun, Gold and Silver Rays by the Consulate-General of Japan, and express our
sincere appreciation for his distinguished public service to his community and this State.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
- 2 - 010676

the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
